<TITLE> Quick action douses Rifles Square fire </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 29 (bdnews24.com)  A fire at the BDR-owned Rifles Square shopping centre, adjacent to the Peelkhana headquarters, was quickly doused due to fast action by security guards and firefighters on Monday. The flames originated at a fast-food shop on the fourth floor, and was put out before it could spread to other shops. Two fire-fighting units rushed to the site, while two security guards had already taken action to stop the fire spreading with the assistance of shop workers and others at the shopping mall. "We noticed at around 8:30 pm that smoke was billowing from beneath the shop's shutter," said guard Badruzzaman. "We broke open the padlock and saw the flames." "Firemen soon joined us as we began dousing the fire," he said. bdnews24.com correspondents said there were few people in the mall as it shut at 8pm. But a crowd of onlookers soon gathered around, they said. bdnews24.c
